data.text:
Hey, I searched for my Fruity loops studio projects of my songs and thought why not share with people who are interested and also use FL Studiio

I really would hear what you make out of it. Maybe covers or masterings or other.

Here is the google drive link to a zip file that contains almost all my projects I ever worked on

Semaphore Fruity Loops Studio projects

it's a bit of a mess and I deleted most redundant projects. Sometimes there is ann older version I worked on years prior so I let it in the folder.

Mainly I used the VST's refX Nexus 2 and East West Quantum leap like Gold orchestra, Colossus, Symphonic choirs...

and for drums Vengeance Soundspackets. I couldn't reacreate some projects because the old versions wont work anymore in FL Studio or because I'm terrible with instrument descriptions =D

And I produced almost only in "Pattern" not in "Song" next to the play button, because I'm a FL Studio noob
